urchase of Irish Examiner|date=10 July 2018|via=www.rte.ie}}</ref>)\n\n====Cavan====\n* ''[[Anglo-Celt|The Anglo-Celt]]'' (Owned by [[Celtic Media Group]] <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fora.ie/inm-celtic-media-deal-scrapped-3427715-Jun2017/|title=INM has scrapped a deal to buy a slew of Irish papers. Here's what you need to know|website=Fora.ie}}</ref>).\n\n====Clare====\n* ''[[The Clare Champion]]'' (Owned by the Galvin family <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/business/clare-newspaper-s-editor-resigns-1.409102|title=Clare newspaper's editor resigns|website=The Irish Times}}</ref>)<ref>https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/deep-sadness-as-the-clare-people-publishes-final-print-edition-with-loss-of-16-jobs-38399929.html</ref>\n* ''The Clare Echo <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejournal.ie/clare-echo-4566947-Mar2019/|title=CCTV footage shows delivery workers for Clare newspaper damaged bundle of rival papers|first=Michelle|last=Hennessy|website=TheJournal.ie}}</ref><ref>https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/deep-sadness-as-the-clare-people-publishes-final-print-edition-with-loss-of-16-jobs-38399929.html</ref>\n*''The Clare County Express Est. 1979''\n\n====Cork====\n* ''The Avondhu''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.avondhupress.ie|title=THE AVONDHU \u2013 News from Cork, Waterford, Limerick and Tipperary|website=The Avondhu Newspaper|accessdate=25 August 2018}}</ref> \u2013 North-East Cork and neighbouring areas of Limerick, Tipperary, Waterford\n* ''Ballincollig News''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.facebook.com/pages/Ballincollig-News/409537639138880|title=Ballincollig News|website=Facebook.com|accessdate=25 August 2018}}</ref> \u2013 Free tabloid monthly newspaper for Ballincollig, County Cork, sister publication of Bishopstown News\n* ''Bishopstown News''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.facebook.com/pages/Bishopstown-News/173613445989043|title=Bishopstown News|website=Facebook.com|accessdate=25 August 2018}}</ref> \u2013 Free monthly newspaper for the Western Suburbs (mainly Bishopstown and Wilton) of Cork City\n* ''[[Carrigdhoun (newspaper)|The Carrigdhoun]]'' \u2013 Carrigaline and South-East Cork <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.carrigdhoun.com/|title=Elections 2019: Se\u00e1mus McGrath \u2013 Fianna F\u00e1il|website=Carrigdhoun Newspaper}}</ref>\n* ''[[Cork Independent (newspaper)|Cork Independent]]'' \u2013 free Cork city and county based weekly newspaper\n* ''The Cork News'' \u2013 free Cork city based weekly newspaper, launched 18 September 2009<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thecorknews.ie/|title=Parallels H-Sphere|website=Thecorknews.ie|accessdate=25 August 2018}}</ref>\n* ''[[The Corkman]]'' (Owned by [[Independent News and Media]] <ref name=\"independent.ie\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.ie/regionals/|title=Irish Regional Newspapers \u2013 Leading Publications.|website=Independent.ie}}</ref>)\n* ''The Douglas Post'' \u2013 weekly magazine for Douglas, Cork <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.douglaspost.ie/about|title=The Douglas Post &#124; Latest Issue|website=www.douglaspost.ie}}</ref>\n* ''East Cork Journal''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eastcorkjournal.ie|title=East Cork Journal \u2013 Only weekly newspaper in East Cork|website=Eastcorkjournal.ie|accessdate=25 August 2018}}</ref> \u2013 launched September 2007\n* ''[[The Echo (Cork newspaper)]]'' (Owned by [[The Irish Times]])\n* ''The Mallow Star'' (Owned by VSO Publications<ref name=\"vsopublicationsltd.ie\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.vsopublicationsltd.ie/category/mallow-star/|title=Category Archives: Mallow Star}}</ref>)\n* ''Midleton News''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.midletonnews.com|title=Welcome to Midleton News|first=Michael|last=McCarthy|website=Midletonnews.com|accessdate=25 August 2018}}</ref> \u2013 A4 size fortnightly newspaper for Midleton County Cork, sister publication of Youghal News, originally free, now retails for one Euro\n* ''The Muskerry News''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.muskerrynews.biz|title=Muskerry News|website=Mu