{"title_page": "Songara", "text_new": "{{short description|Clan of Rajput caste in India}}\n{{refimprove|date=June 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2018}}\n'''Songara''' or '''Songira''' is the name of a branch of the [[Chauhan]] clan of [[Rajputs]].\n\n[[Kirtipala]], the first Chahamana ruler of Jalor ruled his domains from Suvarnagiri or Sonagiri, the hill on which [[Jalore Fort|Jalor Fort]] is located. Because of this, the branch to which he belonged came to be known as Sonagara or Songara.{{sfn|Srivastava|1979|pp=1-2}} The Jalor branch ended with [[Kanhadadeva]], who was defeated and killed by the forces of [[Alauddin Khalji]].\n\n== Clans ==\n\nSongara Rajputs belong to the Agnivanshi group of Rajputs, who claim descent from [[Agni]], the Vedic god of fire. Their sub-clans include:\n\n#Maansinghot Sonigara<ref>Archibald Adams, The western Rajputana states: a medico-topographical and general account, page 60</ref>\n#Bhansinghot Sonigara\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n=== Bibliography ===\n\n* {{cite book |title=The Chahamanas of Jalor |first=Ashok Kumar |last=Srivastava |publisher=Sahitya Sansar Prakashan |year=1979 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Vfi1AAAAIAAJ |ref=harv }}\n* {{cite book | url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=0bkMAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA451 | title=Gazetteer of the Bombay Presidency | volume=1 | issue=1 | publisher=Government Central Press | location=India | year=1896 | page=451 | accessdate=17 November 2018 }} Note 4.\n\n[[Category:Rajput clans]]\n[[Category:Jalore district]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Clan of Rajput caste in India}}\n{{refimprove|date=June 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2018}}\n'''Songara''' or '''Songira''' is the name of a branch of the [[Chauhan]] clan of [[Rajputs]].hawati.\n\n[[Kirtipala]], the first Chahamana ruler of Jalor ruled his domains from Suvarnagiri or Sonagiri, the hill on which [[Jalore Fort|Jalor Fort]] is located. Because of this, the branch to which he belonged came to be known as Sonagara or Songara.{{sfn|Srivastava|1979|pp=1-2}} The Jalor branch ended with [[Kanhadadeva]], who was defeated and killed by the forces of [[Alauddin Khalji]].\n\n== Clans ==\n\nSongara Rajputs belong to the Agnivanshi group of Rajputs, who claim descent from [[Agni]], the Vedic god of fire. Their sub-clans include:\n\n#Maansinghot Sonigara<ref>Archibald Adams, The western Rajputana states: a medico-topographical and general account, page 60</ref>\n#Bhansinghot Sonigara\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n=== Bibliography ===\n\n* {{cite book |title=The Chahamanas of Jalor |first=Ashok Kumar |last=Srivastava |publisher=Sahitya Sansar Prakashan |year=1979 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Vfi1AAAAIAAJ |ref=harv }}\n* {{cite book | url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=0bkMAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA451 | title=Gazetteer of the Bombay Presidency | volume=1 | issue=1 | publisher=Government Central Press | location=India | year=1896 | page=451 | accessdate=17 November 2018 }} Note 4.\n\n[[Category:Rajput clans]]\n[[Category:Jalore district]]\n", "name_user": "PawanjiGupta", "label": "safe", "comment": "Cleaned", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Songara"}
