o City |url=https://news.mb.com.ph/2020/03/22/2-covid-19-cases-confirmed-in-davao-city/ |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=Manila Bulletin |date=March 22, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"MB-CovidDavaoRegion\" />\n**[[Davao de Oro]]<ref name=\"MB-CovidDavaoRegion\">{{cite news |last1=Valdez |first1=Warren |title=Davao Region COVID-19 Update: 50 positive cases; six fatalities |url=https://news.mb.com.ph/2020/03/31/davao-region-covid-19-update-50-positive-cases-six-fatalities/ |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=Manila Bulletin |date=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Davao del Norte]]<ref name=\"MB-CovidDavaoRegion\" />\n**[[Davao del Sur]]<ref name=\"MB-CovidDavaoRegion\" />\n**[[Davao Oriental]]<ref name=\"MB-CovidDavaoRegion\" />\n*[[Soccsksargen]] (Region XII)\n**[[Cotabato]]<ref>{{cite news |title=North Cotabato reports 1st Covid-19 positive case |url=https://www.pna.gov.ph/articles/1098930 |accessdate=April 7, 2020 |agency=Philippine News Agency |date=April 7, 2020}}</ref>\n**''[[General Santos]]''<ref name=\"gensan\">{{cite news |title=General Santos City reports first COVID-19 case |url=https://www.cnnphilippines.com/regional/2020/4/8/general-santos-city-covid-19.html |accessdate=April 8, 2020 |work=CNN Philippines |date=April 8, 2020}}</ref>\n**[[South Cotabato]]<ref name=\"PNAGovPH-CovidSouthCotabato\">{{cite news |last1=Osano |first1=Roel |title=South Cotabato confirms 1st positive Covid-19 case |url=https://www.pna.gov.ph/articles/1098326 |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=Philippine News Agency |date=March 31, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n**[[Sultan Kudarat]]<ref>{{cite news |title=With confirmed COVID-19 case, Sultan Kudarat to impose lockdown, curfew |url=https://www.mindanews.com/top-stories/2020/03/with-confirmed-covid-19-case-sultan-kudarat-to-impose-lockdown-curfew/ |accessdate=March 30, 2020 |work=MindaNews |date=March 27, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Caraga]] (Region XIII)\n**''[[Butuan]]''{{refn|group=note|name=Butuan cases|Sole case admitted to the Caraga Regional Hospital in [[Surigao City]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://cnnphilippines.com/regional/2020/4/6/caraga-all-regions-covid-19-cases.html|title=Caraga reports first COVID-19 case|work=CNN Philippines|date=April 6, 2020|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"caraganolonger\">{{cite news |last1=Panganiban |first1=Chris |title=Caraga region no longer COVID-19 free |url=https://www.mindanews.com/top-stories/2020/04/caraga-region-no-longer-covid-19-free/ |accessdate=April 7, 2020 |work=MindaNews |date=April 6, 2020}}</ref>}}\n**[[Surigao del Norte]]{{refn|group=note|name=Surigao del Norte cases|Sole case imported from Butuan<ref name=\"caraganolonger\"/>}}\n*[[Bangsamoro]] (BARMM)\n**''[[Cotabato City]]''<ref name=\"PIAGovPH-CovidCotabatoCity\">{{cite news |title=Cotabato City records first COVID 19 case in R12 |url=https://pia.gov.ph/news/articles/1036522 |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=Philippine Information Agency |agency=PIA Cotabato City |date=March 18, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>{{refn|group=note|name=Cotabato City region|The Department of Health regional office in Soccsksargen counts cases in the city since the locality was not yet formally turned over to the Bangsamoro regional government.}}\n**[[Lanao del Sur]]<ref name=\"ABS-CBN-CovidLanaoDelSur\">{{cite news |last1=Butardo |first1=Maria Cecilia |title=COVID-19 positive patient dies in Lanao del Sur |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/03/17/20/covid-19-positive-patient-dies-in-lanao-del-sur |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=ABS-CBN News |date=March 17, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n**[[Maguindanao]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Maguindanao confirms first COVID-19 case |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/04/07/20/maguindanao-confirms-first-covid-19-case |accessdate=April 7, 2020 |work=ABS-CBN News |date=April 7, 2020}}</ref>\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Notes ==\n;Map Note\n{{reflist|group=map note}}\n;Other notes\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[2009 swine flu pandemic in the Philippines]]\n\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Philippines|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category}}\n* [http://www.covid19.gov.ph/ Philippine Government's Online Portal for the COVID-19 pandemic].\n* [https://ncovtracker.doh.gov.ph/ COVID-19 case and situation tracker] by the [[Department of Health (Philippines)|Department of Health]]\n* [http://www.ndrrmc.gov.ph/9-ndrrmc-advisory/4036-situational-report-re-national-task-force-for-coronavirus-disease-2019 National Task Force (NTF) for Coronavirus Disease-2019 (COVID-19) Situation Reports]  (Since April 1, [[National Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Council]] website)\n* [http://www.ndrrmc.gov.ph/8-ndrrmc-update/4031-situational-report-re-coronavirus-disease-2019-covid-19 Coronavirus Disease-2019 (COVID-19) Situation Reports] by the [[National Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Council]] (March 13\u201329, 2020)\n* [https://corona.arrangy.com Worldwide Coronavirus Map, confirmed Cases] \u2013 Map the route paths of coronavirus confirmed cases.\n* [https://endcov.ph/dashboard/ University of the Philippines COVID-19 case tracker]\n* [https://covid19ph.com/ Unofficial COVID-19 Philippines data and case tracker]\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Philippines}}\n{{Rodrigo Duterte}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Philippines]]\n[[Category:2020 disasters in the Philippines|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Asia|Philippines]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Philippines| ]]\n", "name_user": "PH 0447", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_the_Philippines"}
{"title_page": "Toyota New Global Architecture", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates |date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox automobile platform\n| name = Toyota New Global Architecture\n| manufacturer = [[Toyota]]\n| production = 2015\u2013present\n| predecessor = {{unbulleted list\n  | [[Toyota B platform]] (TNGA-B)  \n  | [[Toyota MC platform|Toyota MC/New MC platform]] (TNGA-C)\n  | [[Toyota K platform]] (TNGA-K)\n  | [[Toyota N platform]] (TNGA-N/L)\n  }}\n}}\n\nThe '''Toyota New Global Architecture''' ('''TNGA''') are modular [[Vehicle frame#Unibody|unibody]] [[automobile platform]]s that underpin various [[Toyota]] and [[Lexus]] models starting with the fourth generation [[Toyota Prius (XW50)|Prius]] in late 2015.<ref>{{cite web |last=Stocklosa |first=Alexander |date=27 March 2015 |url=http://blog.caranddriver.com/cowa-tnga-toyotas-new-modular-platform-reaching-production-this-year/ |title=Cowa-TNGA! Toyota's New Modular Platform Reaching Production This Year |work=[[Car and Driver]] |access-date=5 August 2016}}</ref> TNGA platforms accommodate different vehicle sizes and also [[Front-wheel drive|front-]], [[Rear-wheel drive|rear-]] and [[Four-wheel drive|all-wheel drive]] configurations.<ref>{{cite web |last=Akita |first=Masahiro |date=11 March 2013 |url=https://doc.research-and-analytics.csfb.com/docView?language=ENG&source=ulg&format=PDF&document_id=1012009391&serialid=XdfQ4rJu3UA%2FZdiFZ4S6lYpBLucxhqiEFJe3A8Ytb8k%3D |title=Opportunities and risks related to parts sourcing for next-gen Prius |publisher=[[Credit Suisse]] |pages=1\u20133 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140717151158/https://doc.research-and-analytics.csfb.com/docView?language=ENG&source=ulg&format=PDF&document_id=1012009391&serialid=XdfQ4rJu3UA%2FZdiFZ4S6lYpBLucxhqiEFJe3A8Ytb8k%3D |archive-date=17 July 2014}}</ref>\n\n== Applications ==\n\n=== {{anchor|GA-B}} TNGA-B (GA-B) ===\nReplaces the [[Toyota B platform|B platform]]. Smaller than TNGA-C and offered in subcompact size with [[transverse engine]] and front- or all-wheel drive.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.motor1.com/news/369058/toyota-tgna-small-vehicle-platform/ |title=Toyota Announces New TNGA Small Car Platform, Likely For Next-Gen Yaris |first=Chris |last=Bruce |work=Motor1 |location=US |date=5 September 2019 |access-date=9 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite press |url=https://newsroom.toyota.eu/toyota-brings-tnga-to-small-cars-with-new-ga-b-platform/ |title=Toyota Brings TNGA To Small Cars With New GA-B Platform |publisher=Toyota |location=Europe |date=5 September 2019 |access-date=9 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''Calendar years''':\n* 2020\u2013present [[Toyota Yaris (XP210)|Toyota Yaris]] (XP210)<ref>{{cite press release |url=https://global.toyota/en/newsroom/toyota/29933748.html |title=Toyota's New Model Yaris Makes World Premiere |publisher=Toyota |date=16 October 2019 |access-date=21 December 2019}}</ref>\n** 2020\u2013present [[Toyota GR Yaris]] (XP210) (with the rear from GA-C platform)<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.motoring.com.au/toyota-gr-yaris-officially-revealed-122379/ |title=Toyota GR Yaris officially revealed |work=Motoring |location=Australia |date=10 January 2020 |access-date=15 January 2020}}</ref>\n* Unnamed B-segment crossover SUV<ref>{{cite press release |url=https://newsroom.toyota.eu/toyota-announces-new-compact-suv-for-its-european-line-up/ |title=Toyota announces new compact SUV for its European line-up |publisher=Toyota |location=Europe |date=14 January 2020 |access-date=15 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n<gallery widths=\"200\" heights=\"150\">\nToyota_YARiS_1.5_G_2WD\u30fbCVT_(5BA-MXPA10-AHXGB)_front.jpg|Toyota Yaris\nToyota GR YARiS RZ\"High-performance\u30fbFirst Edition\" (1).jpg|2020 Toyota GR Yaris RZ High-Performance First Edition (Japan)|Toyota GR Yaris\n</gallery>\n\n=== {{anchor|GA-C}} TNGA-C (GA-C) ===\nReplaces the [[Toyota MC platform|MC and New MC platforms]]. Offered in compact size with transverse engine and front- or all-wheel drive.\n\n'''Calendar years''':\n* 2015\u2013present [[Toyota Prius (XW50)|Toyota Prius]] (XW50)<ref>{{cite web |last=Dowling |first=Neil |date=8 March 2016 |url=http://www.goauto.com.au/mellor/mellor.nsf/story2/4E05804C5010E684CA257F70000CF363 |title=Driven: Reset for Toyota's Prius hybrid king |work=GoAuto |access-date=14 March 2016}}</ref>\n* 2016\u2013present [[Toyota Prius Plug-in Hybrid#XW50|Toyota Prius Plug-in Hybrid]]/[[Toyota Prius Prime|Prime]] (XW50)<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.caranddriver.com/reviews/2018-toyota-prius-prime-in-depth-model-review |title=2018 Toyota Prius Prime {{!}} In-Depth Model Review |first=Annie |last=White |work=Car and Driver |location=US |date=December 2017 |access-date=30 May 2018}}</ref>\n* 2016\u2013present [[Toyota C-HR]]/[[Toyota IZOA|IZOA]] (AX10)<ref>{{cite web |last=Ogbac |first=Stefan |date=8 March 2016 |url=http://www.motortrend.com/news/report-toyota-c-hr-moved-to-tnga-platform-midway-through-development/ |title=Report: Toyota C-HR moved to TNGA platform midway through development |work=[[Motor Trend]] |access-date=14 March 2016}}</ref>\n* 2018\u2013present [[Toyota Corolla (E210)|Toyota Corolla]]/[[Toyota Auris#E210|Auris]]/[[Toyota Corolla (E210)#Sedan|Levin]] (E210)<ref>{{cite press release |url=https://newsroom.toyota.eu/2018-new-auris/ |title=New Auris |publisher=Toyota Europe |location=Geneva |date=6 March 2018 |access-date=9 March 2018}}</ref>\n* 2018\u2013present [[Lexus UX]] (ZA10)<ref>{{cite press release |url=https://newsroom.toyota.co.jp/en/lexus/21357143.html |title=World Debut of the Lexus UX, a New Genre of Crossover |publisher=Toyota |location=Japan |date=6 March 2018 |access-date=9 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n<gallery widths=\"200\" heights=\"150\">\n2016 Toyota Prius (ZVW50R) Hybrid liftback (2016-04-02) 01.jpg|Toyota Prius\n2019 Toyota Prius Business Edition+ PHEV 1.8.jpg|Toyota Prius Plug-in Hybrid\n2017 Toyota Prius Prime front 6.20.18.jpg|Toyota Prius Prime\n2018 Toyota C-HR (NGX50R) Koba AWD hatchback (2018-08-27) 01.jpg|Toyota C-HR