se]] |pages=1\u20133 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140717151158/https://doc.research-and-analytics.csfb.com/docView?language=ENG&source=ulg&format=PDF&document_id=1012009391&serialid=XdfQ4rJu3UA%2FZdiFZ4S6lYpBLucxhqiEFJe3A8Ytb8k%3D |archive-date=17 July 2014}}</ref>\n\n== Applications ==\n\n=== {{anchor|GA-B}} TNGA-B (GA-B) ===\nReplaces the [[Toyota B platform|B platform]]. Smaller than TNGA-C and offered in subcompact size with [[transverse engine]] and front- or all-wheel drive.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.motor1.com/news/369058/toyota-tgna-small-vehicle-platform/ |title=Toyota Announces New TNGA Small Car Platform, Likely For Next-Gen Yaris |first=Chris |last=Bruce |work=Motor1 |location=US |date=5 September 2019 |access-date=9 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite press |url=https://newsroom.toyota.eu/toyota-brings-tnga-to-small-cars-with-new-ga-b-platform/ |title=Toyota Brings TNGA To Small Cars With New GA-B Platform |publisher=Toyota |location=Europe |date=5 September 2019 |access-date=9 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''Calendar years''':\n* 2020\u2013present [[Toyota Yaris (XP210)|Toyota Yaris]] (XP210)<ref>{{cite press release |url=https://global.toyota/en/newsroom/toyota/29933748.html |title=Toyota's New Model Yaris Makes World Premiere |publisher=Toyota |date=16 October 2019 |access-date=21 December 2019}}</ref>\n** 2020\u2013present [[Toyota GR Yaris]] (XP210) (with the rear from GA-C platform)<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.motoring.com.au/toyota-gr-yaris-officially-revealed-122379/ |title=Toyota GR Yaris officially revealed |work=Motoring |location=Australia |date=10 January 2020 |access-date=15 January 2020}}</ref>\n* Unnamed B-segment crossover SUV<ref>{{cite press release |url=https://newsroom.toyota.eu/toyota-announces-new-compact-suv-for-its-european-line-up/ |title=Toyota announces new compact SUV for its European line-up |publisher=Toyota |location=Europe |date=14 January 2020 |access-date=15 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n<gallery widths=\"200\" heights=\"150\">\nToyota YARIS 1.0 G (5BA-KSP210-AHXGK) front.jpg|Toyota Yaris\nToyota GR YARiS RZ\"High-performance\u30fbFirst Edition\" (1).jpg|2020 Toyota GR Yaris RZ High-Performance First Edition (Japan)|Toyota GR Yaris\n</gallery>\n\n=== {{anchor|GA-C}} TNGA-C (GA-C) ===\nReplaces the [[Toyota MC platform|MC and New MC platforms]]. Offered in compact size with transverse engine and front- or all-wheel drive.\n\n'''Calendar years''':\n* 2015\u2013present [[Toyota Prius (XW50)|Toyota Prius]] (XW50)<ref>{{cite web |last=Dowling |first=Neil |date=8 March 2016 |url=http://www.goauto.com.au/mellor/mellor.nsf/story2/4E05804C5010E684CA257F70000CF363 |title=Driven: Reset for Toyota's Prius hybrid king |work=GoAuto |access-date=14 March 2016}}</ref>\n* 2016\u2013present [[Toyota Prius Plug-in Hybrid#XW50|Toyota Prius Plug-in Hybrid]]/[[Toyota Prius Prime|Prime]] (XW50)<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.caranddriver.com/reviews/2018-toyota-prius-prime-in-depth-model-review |title=2018 Toyota Prius Prime {{!}} In-Depth Model Review |first=Annie |last=White |work=Car and Driver |location=US |date=December 2017 |access-date=30 May 2018}}</ref>\n* 2016\u2013present [[Toyota C-HR]]/[[Toyota IZOA|IZOA]] (AX10)<ref>{{cite web |last=Ogbac |first=Stefan |date=8 March 2016 |url=http://www.motortrend.com/news/report-toyota-c-hr-moved-to-tnga-platform-midway-through-development/ |title=Report: Toyota C-HR moved to TNGA platform midway through development |work=[[Motor Trend]] |access-date=14 March 2016}}</ref>\n* 2018\u2013present [[Toyota Corolla (E210)|Toyota Corolla]]/[[Toyota Auris#E210|Auris]]/[[Toyota Corolla (E210)#Sedan|Levin]] (E210)<ref>{{cite press release |url=https://newsroom.toyota.eu/2018-new-auris/ |title=New Auris |publisher=Toyota Europe |location=Geneva |date=6 March 2018 |access-date=9 March 2018}}</ref>\n* 2018\u2013present [[Lexus UX]] (ZA10)<ref>{{cite press release |url=https://newsroom.toyota.co.jp/en/lexus/21357143.html |title=World Debut of the Lexus UX, a New Genre of Crossover |publisher=Toyota |location=Japan |date=6 March 2018 |access-date=9 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n<gallery widths=\"200\" heights=\"150\">\n2016 Toyota Prius (ZVW50R) Hybrid liftback (2016-04-02) 01.jpg|Toyota Prius\n2019 Toyota Prius Business Edition+ PHEV 1.8.jpg|Toyota Prius Plug-in Hybrid\n2017 Toyota Prius Prime front 6.20.18.jpg|Toyota Prius Prime\n2018 Toyota C-HR (NGX50R) Koba AWD hatchback (2018-08-27) 01.jpg|Toyota C-HR\nToyota C-HR EV 001.jpg|Toyota C-HR EV\nToyota Izoa 01 China 2019-04-03.jpg|Toyota IZOA\nToyota Izoa EV 001.jpg|Toyota IZOA EV\nToyota Corolla Limousine Hybrid Genf 2019 1Y7A5576.jpg|Toyota Corolla sedan (''Prestige'' model)\n2020 Toyota Corolla LE standard front, 5.25.19.jpg|Toyota Corolla sedan (''Sporty'' model)\n2018 Toyota Corolla (ZWE211R) ZR hybrid hatchback (2018-10-30) 01.jpg|Toyota Corolla hatchback\nToyota COROLLA TOURING HYBRID W\u00d7B 2WD (6AA-ZWE211W-AWXSB) front.jpg|Toyota Corolla Touring\nToyota Corolla Hybrid, Paris Motor Show 2018, IMG 0721.jpg|Toyota Corolla Touring Sports\nToyota Auris, GIMS 2018, Le Grand-Saconnex (1X7A1626).jpg|Toyota Auris\nGAC Toyota Levin Hybrid E210 of guangzhou auto show 2018.jpg|Toyota Levin\nLexus, Paris Motor Show 2018, Paris (1Y7A1795).jpg|Lexus UX\n</gallery>\n\n=== {{anchor|GA-K}} TNGA-K (GA-K) ===\nReplaces the [[Toyota K platform|K platform]]. Larger than TNGA-C with transverse engine and front- or all-wheel drive.\n\n'''Calendar years''':\n* 2017\u2013present [[Toyota Camry (XV70)|Toyota Camry]]/[[Daihatsu Altis#XV70|Daihatsu Altis]] (XV70)<ref>{{cite web |last=Booth |first=David |date=10 January 2017 |url=http://driving.ca/toyota/camry/auto-shows/detroit-auto-show/best-selling-toyota-camry-redesigned-for-2018-and-it-actually-looks-good |title=Toyota Camry redesigned for 2018 \u2013 and it actually looks good |work=Driving |access-date=10 January 2017}}</ref>\n* 2018\u2013present [[Toyota Avalon (XX50)|Toyota Avalon]] (XX50)<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://toyotanews.pressroom.toyota.com/releases/attainable+premium+actualized+all+new+2019+toyota+avalon+beams+effortless+sophistication+style.htm |title=Attainable Premium, Actualized: All-New 2019 Toyota Avalon Beams Effortless Sophistication, Style, and Exhilaration at the 2018 North American International Auto Show |publisher=Toyota |location=US |date=15 January 2018 |access-date=30 May 2018}}</ref>\n* 2018\u2013present [[Lexus ES (XZ10)|Lexus ES]] (XZ10)<ref name=\"newes\">{{cite press release |url=https://www.automotiveworld.com/news-releases/new-lexus-es-higher-level-performance-sophistication/ |title=The all-new Lexus ES: a higher level of performance and sophistication |publisher=Automotive World |date=25 April 2018 |access-date=25 April 2018}}</ref>\n* 2018\u2013present [[Toyota RAV4 (XA50)|Toyota RAV4]]/[[Toyota Wildlander|Wildlander]] (XA50)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.toyota-tech.eu/whatsNew.aspx |title=Toyota Service Information \u2013 What's new? |publisher=Toyota |location=Europe |date=19 January 2019 |access-date=19 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite press release |url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/all-new-2019-toyota-rav4-serves-up-a-breakthrough-debut-at-new-york-international-auto-show-300620218.html |title=All-New 2019 Toyota RAV4 Serves Up A Breakthrough Debut At New York International Auto Show |publisher=Toyota |location=US |via=PR Newswire |date=28 March 2018 |access-date=10 May 2018}}</ref>\n* 2019\u2013present [[Toyota Highlander#XU70|Toyota Highlander]] (XU70)<ref>{{cite press release |url=https://pressroom.toyota.com/releases/world-premiere-of-all-new-2020-highlander-at-new-york-international-auto-show.htm |title=World Premiere of All-New 2020 Highlander at New York International Auto Show |publisher=Toyota |location=US |date=17 April 2019 |access-date=17 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.caranddriver.com/news/a27167925/2020-toyota-highlander-photos-info/ |title=The 2020 Toyota Highlander Is a More Chiseled Version of Itself |first=Andrew |last=Wendler |work=Car and Driver |location=US |date=17 April 2019 |access-date=17 April 2019}}</ref>\n* 2020\u2013present [[Toyota Harrier#XU80|Toyota Harrier]] (XU80)<ref>{{cite press release |author= |title=Toyota to Unveil New Model Harrier in Japan |url=https://global.toyota/en/newsroom/toyota/32186311.html |location=Toyota City, Aichi |publisher=Toyota Global Newsroom |date=2020-04-13 |access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Chan |first=Mick |date=2020-04-13 |title=All-new 2020 Toyota Harrier debuts \u2013 TNGA (GA-K) platform, 2.0L petrol, Direct Shift-CVT, no more turbo |url=https://paultan.org/2020/04/13/all-new-2020-toyota-harrier-debuts-tnga-ga-k-platform-2-0-petrol-direct-shift-cvt-no-more-turbo/ |website=Paultan.org |publisher=Driven Communications |location=Malaysia |access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n<gallery widths=\"200\" heights=\"150\">\n2018 Toyota Camry (ASV70R) Ascent sedan (2018-11-02) 01.jpg|Toyota Camry\nDAIHATSU ALTIS AXVH70N 001.jpg|Daihatsu Altis\n2019 Toyota Avalon Touring front 4.2.18.jpg|Toyota Avalon\n2019 Lexus ES 350 3.5L front 3.20.19.jpg|Lexus ES\n2019 Toyota RAV4 XLE AWD, front 12.31.19.jpg|Toyota RAV4\nToyota Wildlander Hybrid.jpg|Toyota Wildlander\n2020 Toyota Highlander Platinum AWD front NYIAS 2019.jpg|Toyota Highlander\n</gallery>\n\n=== {{anchor|GA-N}} TNGA-N (GA-N) ===\nReplaces the [[Toyota N platform|N and New N platforms]]. Offered with [[longitudinal engine]] and rear- or all-wheel drive.\n\n'''Calendar years''':\n* 2018\u2013present [[Toyota Crown (S220)|Toyota Crown]] (S220)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://prius-news.com/1685.html |title=\u30c8\u30e8\u30bf\u306eTNGA\u3068\u306f\u30d7\u30e9\u30c3\u30c8\u30d5\u30a9\u30fc\u30e0\u306e\u3053\u3068\uff1f {{!}} \u6c17\u306b\u306a\u308b\u8eca\u3092\u30af\u30ed\u30fc\u30ba\u30a2\u30c3\u30d7 |trans-title=What is Toyota's TNGA platform? Close up of the car you care about |publisher=Toyota |location=Japan |language=Japanese |date=5 May 2018 |access-date=17 July 2018}}</ref>\n* 2020\u2013present [[Toyota Mirai]]<ref>{{cite press release |url=https://newsroom.toyota.eu/toyota-advances-towards-a-hydrogen-mobility-future-with-second-generation-mirai/ |title=Toyota advances towards a hydrogen mobility future with second generation Mirai |publisher=Toyota |location=Europe |date=14 January 2020 |access-date=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n<gallery widths=\"200\" heights=\"150\">\n2018 Toyota Crown 2.0 S.jpg|Toyota Crown\n</gallery>\n\n=== {{anchor|GA-L}} TNGA-L (GA-L) ===\nThe Global Architecture for Luxury vehicles is used on Lexus vehicles. Offered with longitudinal engine and rear- or all-wheel drive.\n\n'''Calendar years''':\n* 2017\u2013present [[Lexus LC]] (Z100)<ref name=LS>{{cite press release |url=http://pressroom.toyota.com/releases/new-lexus-ls-flagship-sedan-to-debut-2017-naias.htm |title=New Lexus LS Flagship Sedan to Make Global Debut at the 2017 NAIAS |publisher=Toyota |location=US |date=8 December 2016 |access-date=22 December 2016}}</ref>\n* 2017\u2013present [[Lexus LS (XF50)|Lexus LS]] (XF50)<ref name=LS/>\n\n<gallery widths=\"200\" heights=\"150\">\n2017-03-07 Geneva Motor Show 1212.JPG|Lexus LC\n2018 Lexus LS 500 front 2.22.19.jpg|Lexus LS\n</gallery>\n\n== {{anchor|e-TNGA|eTNGA}} e-TNGA ==\nThe ''e-TNGA'' is an [[electric car]] platform that will be applied to 10 dedicated models worldwide (including 6 global models) by early 2020. The six global models include:\n* Compact car (in collaboration with [[Suzuki]] and [[Daihatsu]])\n* Mid-size crossover SUV\n* Mid-size sedan\n* Minivan\n* Mid-size SUV (in collaboration with [[Subaru]])\n* Large SUV\n\nThe platform will enable offering various type and size of vehicles, different battery capacity and with front-wheel drive, rear-wheel drive or dual motor all-wheel drive. This vehicle architecture is partitioned into five modules. These are the front module, center module, rear module, battery and motor. Up to three versions of each module are in development, including three capacities for the [[lithium-ion battery]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://insideevs.com/news/353600/toyota-six-global-bevs/ |title=Toyota Goes Electric Starting In 2020: Announces Massive EV Offensive |first=Mark |last=Kane |work=InsideEVs |location=US |date=7 June 2019 |access-date=9 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.autoevolution.com/news/new-toyota-e-tnga-platform-detailed-every-model-will-be-electrified-by-2025-135060.html |title=New Toyota e-TNGA Platform Detailed, Every Model Will Be Electrified By 2025 |first=Mircea |last=Panait |work=autoevolution |location=Romania  |date=8 June 2019 |access-date=9 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite press release |url=https://media.toyota.co.uk/wp-content/files_mf/1559900303AimingtoPopulariseBEVs.pdf |title=Toyota's Challenge \u2013 Aiming to Popularize BEVs |publisher=Toyota |date=7 June 2019 |access-date=15 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== {{anchor|DNGA}} Daihatsu New Global Architecture ==\nAs Toyota owns 100% of [[Daihatsu]], the ''Daihatsu New Global Architecture'' (DNGA) is derived from TNGA and currently used exclusively in Daihatsu-produced [[kei car]]s and subcompact cars, some of which are sold with Toyota and Subaru badging.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://response.jp/article/2019/06/06/323176.html |title=\u30c0\u30a4\u30cf\u30c4\u306e\u65b0\u958b\u767a\u624b\u6cd5\u300cDNGA\u300d\u7b2c1\u5f3e\u30017\u6708\u767a\u58f2\u306e \u30bf\u30f3\u30c8 \u65b0\u578b\u2026\u4e00\u62ec\u4f01\u753b\u3067\u5c0f\u578b\u8eca\u307e\u3067\u30ab\u30d0\u30fc |trans-title=Daihatsu's new development method \"DNGA\" first, Tanto new model released in July ... Covers even small cars by collective planning |publisher=Response |location=Japan |language=Japanese |date=6 June 2019 |access-date=27 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite press release |url=https://www.daihatsu.com/jp/news/2019/20190606-1.pdf |title=\u30c0\u30a4\u30cf\u30c4\u5de5\u696d \uff24\uff2e\uff27\uff21\u65b0\u6280\u8853\u3092\u516c\u8868\u3000\uff5e\uff17\u6708\